President Donald J. Trump has declared an emergency in the U.S. Virgin Islands due to the conditions caused by Hurricane Dorian. This declaration allows the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) to coordinate disaster relief efforts and provide assistance for emergency measures. FEMA is authorized to mobilize resources and equipment to alleviate the impacts of the emergency. The federal funding for emergency protective measures will be provided at 75 percent. Seamus K. Leary has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations in the affected areas. For more information, media can contact the FEMA news desk.